				<p>A building can be considered a Passivhaus when the energy required for heating or cooling can be only supplied through the ventilation air required to assure a minimum of hygiene in the internal areas.</p>

				<p>This definition is the only one at an international level that is valid regardless the climate. All the other existing standards establish a series of measurement and certification criteria depending on the geographical location of each place. The international definition of Passivhaus explains the success it is achieving all over the world.</p>

